Initialize GIT
#git init

Add user details
git config --global user.name "Mukesh Singh"
git config --global user.email "cz65rv@gmail.com"

Display user details
#git config --global --list

Run below command to save your GIT login credentials.
#git config --global credential.helper store

To remove saved or cached git credetails
#git config --global --unset credential.helper

To add file in staging area
#git add <file-name> or . 

Perform commit for added files 
# git commit -m "Commit msg"

To add remote repository to your local computer
#git add remote https://github.com/cz65rv/lab.git

To remove remote repository to your local computer
#git remote remove https://github.com/cz65rv/lab.git

Pull command will pull the all files from given repository
#git pull https://github.com/cz65rv/nodejs.git

Clone command will not only pull all files from given repository but will add remote repository as well
#git pull https://github.com/cz65rv/nodejs.git

To create branch and move into that branch
#git checkout -b demo

Create branch without moving into it.
#git branch demo















git init
git config --global user.email "cz65rv@gmail.com"
git config --global user.name "Mukesh"
git branch -M main
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/cz65rv/lab.git
git push -u origin main





